original: Ideberg, Tore Edvin, tandläkare, Vänersborg, f. 5/4/01 i Säffle, Värml. I. G. 31 m. Karin Matilda Melin. Barn: Gunnar i. 32, Sven 313’, RoiM 36, Gunnel 43. — Stud:ex. i Vänersborg 19, tandlikand. 21, tandl. 23. Vik. i Borlänge 23, prakt, i Säffle 23-29, i Väners’borg sed. 29. Skattmäst. i Västgöta-Dals tandl :fören. 40-45, ordf. i styr. f. Vänersborgs KFUM scoutkår.
translated: Ideberg, Tore Edvin, dentist, Vänersborg, b. April 5th, 1901 in Säffle, Värmland. Married Karin Matilda Melin in 1931. Children: Gunnar b. 1932, Sven b. 1933, RoiM b. 1936, Gunnel b. 1943. Completed secondary school education in Vänersborg in 1919. Completed dental education in 1921 and became a licensed dentist in 1923. Worked temporarily in Borlänge in 1923, practiced dentistry in Säffle from 1923-1929, and has practiced in Vänersborg since. Served as treasurer of the Västgöta-Dals Dental Association from 1940-1945 and served as chairman of the board of the Vänersborg YMCA Scout Corps.
